<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
  <title>License Application - RCVD</title>
  <style>
    .container {
      max-width: 960px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      background-color: #fff;
    }

    h2 {
      color: #2c3e50;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    .license ul {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      list-style: none;
    }

    .license ul li {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 1.8rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .license ul li::before {
      content: "üìù";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #2c3e50;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .container {
        padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <div class="container license">
    <main>
      <section>
        <h2>License Application</h2>
        <p>
          To apply for a veterinary license, please ensure that the following documents are prepared and submitted as part of your application:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            A license application letter addressed to the Chairperson of the Council, indicating one, two, or three non-conflicting veterinary service types (as per Article 2), and the preferred zone of practice (district or sector).
          </li>
          <li>
            A copy of the previous license (required for veterinary practitioners already licensed).
          </li>
          <li>
            A recent color passport photo.
          </li>
          <li>
            Proof of payment of the annual licensing fee:
            <br>‚Äì 60,000 RWF for BSc, DVM, MSc, PhD holders
            <br>‚Äì 40,000 RWF for A2 and A1 diploma holders
          </li>
          <li>
            Proof of participation in CPD (Continuing Professional Development) activities during the current license validity period:
            <br>‚Äì Minimum of 20 credit points per CPD year for veterinary professionals
            <br>‚Äì Minimum of 14 credit points per CPD year for veterinary paraprofessionals
          </li>
          <li>
            Certificate of registration in the country of origin and its official translation (if applicable).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
